    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Pick a Threshold to Maximize F1 Score\n",
        "\n",
        "In campaign 3, we have a limited campaign budget. We want to maximize the number of responses while minimizing the number of prospects who are sent direct mail.\n",
        "\n",
        "One approach is to select a threshold that maximizes the F1 score.\n",
        "\n",
        "First, we check the F1 score for the default threshold of `0.5`."
      ],
      "id": "c1d82b10"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-score-f1-thresholds\n",
        "df_leaders_f1 = (ag_model\n",
        "            .named_steps['autogluon']\n",
        "            .predictor\n",
        "            .leaderboard(\n",
        "                test_data, \n",
        "                extra_metrics=['f1', 'precision', 'recall'])\n",
        "            )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-score-f1-thresholds",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-ag-leaderboard-f1\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Autogluon Leaderboard with F1 Score (Threshold = 0.5)\n",
        "\n",
        "display(df_leaders_f1)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-ag-leaderboard-f1",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "In order to avoid overfitting, we will use `df_campaign_2` to select the threshold that maximizes the F1 score."
      ],
      "id": "494fe8c2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-select-best-threshold\n",
        "best_threshold = (ag_model\n",
        "                .named_steps['autogluon']\n",
        "                .predictor\n",
        "                .calibrate_decision_threshold(\n",
        "                data = df_campaign_2,\n",
        "                metric = 'f1',\n",
        "                decision_thresholds = 100)\n",
        "                )\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model.named_steps['autogluon'].predictor.set_decision_threshold(best_threshold)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-select-best-threshold",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Finally, we check the F1 score for the new threshold."
      ],
      "id": "24ca23fe"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-show-best-f1-results\n",
        "df_leaders_f1_best = (ag_model\n",
        "            .named_steps['autogluon']\n",
        "            .predictor\n",
        "            .leaderboard(\n",
        "                test_data, \n",
        "                extra_metrics=['f1', 'precision', 'recall'])\n",
        "            )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-show-best-f1-results",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-ag-leaderboard-f1-best\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Autogluon Leaderboard with F1 Score (Best Threshold)\n",
        "\n",
        "display(df_leaders_f1_best)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-ag-leaderboard-f1-best",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Select Targets\n",
        "\n",
        "We randomly select `1,000` prospects as a control group. We will send direct mail to everyone in the control group. The control group gives us a baseline response rate."
      ],
      "id": "9a101d27"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-select-control-group\n",
        "# Randomly select 1000 prospects for control group\n",
        "df_campaign_3_control_group = df_campaign_3.sample(n=1000, random_state=2025)\n",
        "\n",
        "df_campaign_3_control_group['group_type'] = 'control'\n",
        "df_campaign_3_control_group['direct_mail_flag'] = 'Y'"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-select-control-group",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Create `df_campaign_3_treatment` by removing the control group from `df_campaign_3`."
      ],
      "id": "c1bc58bc"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-define-treatment-group\n",
        "df_campaign_3_treatment = df_campaign_3.drop(df_campaign_3_control_group.index)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-define-treatment-group",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Then, we send direct mail to all the prospects in `df_campaign_3_treatment` that exceed the best threshold. We are assuming that the prospects in `df_campaign_3_treatment` meet the other campaign selection criteria that were determined by the risk, strategy, and legal teams."
      ],
      "id": "e0dd2b52"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-score-treatment-group\n",
        "X_campaign3 = df_campaign_3_treatment[subset_cols].copy()\n",
        "X_campaign3['last_prod_enq2'] = X_campaign3['last_prod_enq2'].astype('category')\n",
        "\n",
        "preds = ag_model.predict(X_campaign3.drop(columns=[label]))\n",
        "\n",
        "df_campaign_3_treatment['direct_mail_flag'] = np.where(preds == 1, 'Y', 'N')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Filter to only keep prospects that will receive direct mail\n",
        "df_campaign_3_treatment_mail = df_campaign_3_treatment[df_campaign_3_treatment['direct_mail_flag'] == 'Y'].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "df_campaign_3_treatment_mail['group_type'] = 'treatment'\n",
        "\n",
        "# Append rows from controls and treatment into a single data frame\n",
        "keep_cols = ['PROSPECTID', 'campaign_id', 'group_type', 'direct_mail_flag']    \n",
        "\n",
        "df_campaign_3_selected = (pd.concat([\n",
        "        df_campaign_3_control_group[keep_cols], \n",
        "        df_campaign_3_treatment_mail[keep_cols]\n",
        "        ],\n",
        "    ignore_index=True)\n",
        "    .reset_index(drop=True))"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-score-treatment-group",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Measure Campaign Effectiveness\n",
        "\n",
        "The file `campaign_eval.parquet` contains the results of the campaign. We will join the data set with df_campaign_3_selected to measure the effectiveness of the campaign."
      ],
      "id": "4fdbc583"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-build-campaign-eval-data\n",
        "df_campaign_eval = duckdb.query(\"\"\"\n",
        "    SELECT SELECTED.*, EVAL.response_flag\n",
        "    FROM read_parquet('../Data/cibil/campaign_eval.parquet') AS EVAL\n",
        "    INNER JOIN df_campaign_3_selected AS SELECTED\n",
        "    ON EVAL.PROSPECTID = SELECTED.PROSPECTID\n",
        "    ORDER BY SELECTED.group_type, SELECTED.PROSPECTID\n",
        "\"\"\").to_df()"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-build-campaign-eval-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-campaign-top5-eval\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: First 5 rows of df_campaign_eval\n",
        "\n",
        "df_campaign_eval.head()"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-campaign-top5-eval",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Summarize the results."
      ],
      "id": "cd0e3718"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-summarize-campaign-results\n",
        "df_eval_agg = (df_campaign_eval\n",
        "    .groupby(['group_type', 'direct_mail_flag'])\n",
        "    .agg({\n",
        "        'response_flag': ['count', 'sum', 'mean']\n",
        "    })\n",
        "    .reset_index()\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "df_eval_agg.columns = ['group_type', 'direct_mail_flag', 'prospects', 'responses', 'response_rate']"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-summarize-campaign-results",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-campaign-agg\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Campaign Effectiveness\n",
        "\n",
        "display(df_eval_agg)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-campaign-agg",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Measure Campaign ROI\n",
        "\n",
        "The treatment group has a much higher response rate than the control group. The ROI of the treatment group is also much higher than the ROI of the control group.\n",
        "\n",
        "The ROI calculation is based on the following assumptions:\n",
        "\n",
        "-   The average cost depends on whether the prospect was sent direct mail:\n",
        "    -   Each prospect (regardless of whether they were sent direct mail) costs \\$1.00.\n",
        "    -   Each prospect that was sent direct mail incurs an *additional* \\$6.00 cost.\n",
        "-   The average revenue from a response is \\$100.00.\n",
        "\n",
        "In prior campaigns, the average cost was \\$7.00 per prospect because *all* prospects were sent direct mail. In this campaign, we are sending direct mail to only a subset of prospects."
      ],
      "id": "31a147ec"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-define-roi-function\n",
        "def calc_ROI(num_mailed, \n",
        "            num_responded, \n",
        "            avg_mail_cost, \n",
        "            avg_revenue, \n",
        "            num_prospects, \n",
        "            avg_prospect_cost):\n",
        "    total_cost = (num_mailed * avg_mail_cost) + (num_prospects * avg_prospect_cost)\n",
        "    total_revenue = num_responded * avg_revenue\n",
        "    roi = (total_revenue - total_cost) / total_cost * 100\n",
        "    return roi"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-define-roi-function",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-calculate-campaign-roi\n",
        "roi_control = calc_ROI(num_mailed = 1000,\n",
        "                        num_responded = 49, \n",
        "                        avg_mail_cost = 6,\n",
        "                        avg_revenue = 100,\n",
        "                        num_prospects = 1000,\n",
        "                        avg_prospect_cost = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "roi_treatment = calc_ROI(num_mailed = 4338,\n",
        "                        num_responded = 1625, \n",
        "                        avg_mail_cost = 6,\n",
        "                        avg_revenue = 100,\n",
        "                        num_prospects = 95889 - 1000,\n",
        "                        avg_prospect_cost = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Control Group ROI: {roi_control:.2f}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"Treatment Group ROI: {roi_treatment:.2f}%\")"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-calculate-campaign-roi",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Feature Reduction Methods\n",
        "\n",
        "Up until now, we used only a small subset of the features."
      ],
      "id": "97bdb643"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
