    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "We will now widen the data frames to include more features, and explore feature reduction methods.\n",
        "\n",
        "We need to remove features that are protected by US law."
      ],
      "id": "d59a3385"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-define-protected-features\n",
        "protected_features = ['MARITALSTATUS', 'AGE', 'GENDER']"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-define-protected-features",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-build-wide-training-data\n",
        "train_data_wide = df_campaign_1_train.copy().drop(columns=protected_features)\n",
        "test_data_wide = df_campaign_1_test.copy().drop(columns=protected_features)\n",
        "\n",
        "train_data_wide = TabularDataset(train_data_wide)\n",
        "test_data_wide = TabularDataset(test_data_wide)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-build-wide-training-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-campaign-1-train-full\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: First 5 rows of train_data_wide\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "train_data_wide.head()"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-campaign-1-train-full",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-campaign-1-test-full\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: First 5 rows of test_data_wide\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "test_data_wide.head()"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-campaign-1-test-full",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Filter-based Methods\n",
        "\n",
        "Filter-based methods select features by evaluating the relationship between each individual feature and the target outcome. The selected features are then fed into a machine learning algorithm like XGBoost. Filter-based methods:\n",
        "\n",
        "-   Rank features using statistical measures (correlation, mutual information, chi-square tests)\n",
        "-   Select top-ranked features\n",
        "-   Are computationally efficient\n",
        "-   Consider each feature independently, potentially missing important feature interactions\n",
        "\n",
        "The chunk below creates a scikit-learn pipeline that uses `SelectKBest` to select the top 10 features based on mutual information. The top 10 features are then used to train an `autogluon` model."
      ],
      "id": "390f03c5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-define-selectkbest-wrapper\n",
        "class IndexPreservingSelectKBest(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, score_func=mutual_info_classif, k=10):\n",
        "        self.score_func = score_func\n",
        "        self.k = k\n",
        "        self.selector = SelectKBest(score_func=score_func, k=k)\n",
        "        \n",
        "    def fit(self, X, y=None):\n",
        "        self.selector.fit(X, y)\n",
        "        return self\n",
        "        \n",
        "    def transform(self, X):\n",
        "        # Transform while preserving index\n",
        "        Xt = self.selector.transform(X)\n",
        "        return pd.DataFrame(Xt, index=X.index)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-define-selectkbest-wrapper",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-fit-filter-method-model\n",
        "# remove ag folder if exists\n",
        "filter_model_folder = 'Lab01_ag_models_FilterMethod'\n",
        "remove_ag_folder(filter_model_folder)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ensures that the output after is transformation is a data frame\n",
        "set_config(transform_output=\"pandas\")\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_filter_method = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('replace_values', FunctionTransformer(replace_vals)),\n",
        "    ('ordinal_encoder', make_column_transformer(\n",
        "        (OrdinalEncoder(), make_column_selector(dtype_include=[\"object\", \"category\"])),\n",
        "        remainder='passthrough'\n",
        "    )),\n",
        "    ('feature_selection', IndexPreservingSelectKBest(score_func=mutual_info_classif, k=10)),\n",
        "    ('autogluon', AutoGluonSklearnWrapper(label=label,\n",
        "                                    predictor_args={'problem_type': 'binary',\n",
        "                                                    'eval_metric': 'roc_auc',\n",
        "                                                    'path': filter_model_folder},\n",
        "                                    fit_args={'holdout_frac': 0.2,\n",
        "                                                'excluded_model_types': ['KNN', 'NN_TORCH'],\n",
        "                                                'presets': 'medium_quality',\n",
        "                                                'time_limit': 180}))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "global_set_seed()\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_filter_method.fit( X = train_data_wide.drop(\n",
        "                    columns=[label] + ['PROSPECTID', 'campaign_id', 'direct_mail_flag']),\n",
        "            y = train_data_wide[label]\n",
        "            )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-fit-filter-method-model",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Check leaderboard using the test set."
      ],
      "id": "58de0e0a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-transform-filter-test-data\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data = ag_model_filter_method[:-1].transform(test_data_wide)\n",
        "\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data[label] = test_data_wide[label]\n",
        "\n",
        "df_leaders_filter_method = ag_model_filter_method.named_steps['autogluon'].predictor.leaderboard(preprocessed_test_data)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-transform-filter-test-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-ag-leaderboard-filter-method\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Autogluon Leaderboard (Filter-based Method)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "display(df_leaders_filter_method)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-ag-leaderboard-filter-method",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Check permutation feature importance on the test set."
      ],
      "id": "bba5306d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-compute-filter-importance\n",
        "best_feature_importance_filter = (ag_model_filter_method\n",
        "                            .named_steps['autogluon']\n",
        "                            .predictor\n",
        "                            .feature_importance(\n",
        "                                    data = preprocessed_test_data, \n",
        "                                    model = best_model_name,\n",
        "                                    subsample_size = None)\n",
        "                        )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-compute-filter-importance",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-perm-feature-importance-filter-method\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Permutation Feature Importance (Filter-based Method)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "display(best_feature_importance_filter)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-perm-feature-importance-filter-method",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Embedded Methods\n",
        "\n",
        "Embedded methods integrate feature selection directly into the model training/fitting process:\n",
        "\n",
        "-   Select features while the model is being trained/fitted\n",
        "-   Balance feature relevance with model performance\n",
        "-   Have moderate computational cost\n",
        "-   Examples: L1 regularization (Lasso), tree-based importance measures\n",
        "\n",
        "The chunk below creates a scikit-learn pipeline that uses `SelectFromModel` and the `ExtraTreesClassifier` to select the top features. The top features are then used to train an `autogluon` model."
      ],
      "id": "450c3dc4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-fit-embedded-method-model\n",
        "# remove ag folder if exists\n",
        "embedded_model_folder = 'Lab01_ag_models_EmbeddedMethod'\n",
        "remove_ag_folder(embedded_model_folder)\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_embedded_method = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('replace_values', FunctionTransformer(replace_vals)),\n",
        "    ('ordinal_encoder', make_column_transformer(\n",
        "        (OrdinalEncoder(), make_column_selector(dtype_include=[\"object\", \"category\"])),\n",
        "        remainder='passthrough'\n",
        "    )),\n",
        "    ('feature_selection', SelectFromModel(\n",
        "        ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=2025, criterion='entropy', max_depth=3, n_jobs=-1),\n",
        "        threshold=0.01\n",
        "    )),\n",
        "    ('autogluon', AutoGluonSklearnWrapper(label=label,\n",
        "                                    predictor_args={'problem_type': 'binary',\n",
        "                                                    'eval_metric': 'roc_auc',\n",
        "                                                    'path': embedded_model_folder},\n",
        "                                    fit_args={'holdout_frac': 0.2,\n",
        "                                                'excluded_model_types': ['KNN', 'NN_TORCH'],\n",
        "                                                'presets': 'medium_quality',\n",
        "                                                'time_limit': 180}))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "global_set_seed()\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_embedded_method.fit( X = train_data_wide.drop(\n",
        "                    columns=[label] + ['PROSPECTID', 'campaign_id', 'direct_mail_flag']),\n",
        "            y = train_data_wide[label]\n",
        "            )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-fit-embedded-method-model",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Check leaderboard using the test set."
      ],
      "id": "e11b6366"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-transform-embedded-test-data\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data_embedded = ag_model_embedded_method[:-1].transform(test_data_wide.drop(columns=[label]))\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data_embedded[label] = test_data_wide[label]\n",
        "\n",
        "df_leaders_embedded_method = ag_model_embedded_method.named_steps['autogluon'].predictor.leaderboard(preprocessed_test_data_embedded)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-transform-embedded-test-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-ag-leaderboard-embedded-method\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Autogluon Leaderboard (Embedded Method)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "display(df_leaders_embedded_method)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-ag-leaderboard-embedded-method",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Check permutation feature importance on the test set."
      ],
      "id": "9426dc26"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-compute-embedded-importance\n",
        "best_feature_importance_embedded = (ag_model_embedded_method\n",
        "                            .named_steps['autogluon']\n",
        "                            .predictor\n",
        "                            .feature_importance(\n",
        "                                    data = preprocessed_test_data_embedded, \n",
        "                                    model = best_model_name,\n",
        "                                    subsample_size = None)\n",
        "                        )"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-compute-embedded-importance",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "tbl-number": true
      },
      "source": [
        "#| label: tbl-perm-feature-importance-embedded-method\n",
        "#| tbl-cap: Permutation Feature Importance (Embedded Method)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "display(best_feature_importance_embedded)"
      ],
      "id": "tbl-perm-feature-importance-embedded-method",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Wrapper Methods\n",
        "\n",
        "Wrapper methods evaluate subsets of features by training models with different feature combinations using the same machine learning algorithm:\n",
        "\n",
        "-   Use the predictive performance of a model to evaluate feature subsets\n",
        "-   Can capture feature interactions\n",
        "-   Are computationally expensive\n",
        "-   Examples: recursive feature elimination, forward/backward selection\n",
        "\n",
        "The chunk below creates a scikit-learn pipeline that uses forward selection (`SequentialFeatureSelector`) and `ExtraTreesClassifier` estimator to select the top features. The top features are then used to train an `autogluon` model."
      ],
      "id": "2231f1a6"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-fit-wrapper-method-model\n",
        "# remove ag folder if exists\n",
        "wrapper_model_folder = 'Lab01_ag_models_WrapperMethod'\n",
        "remove_ag_folder(wrapper_model_folder)\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_wrapper_method = Pipeline([\n",
        "    ('replace_values', FunctionTransformer(replace_vals)),\n",
        "    ('ordinal_encoder', make_column_transformer(\n",
        "        (OrdinalEncoder(), make_column_selector(dtype_include=[\"object\", \"category\"])),\n",
        "        remainder='passthrough'\n",
        "    )),\n",
        "    ('feature_selection', SequentialFeatureSelector(\n",
        "        ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=2025, criterion='entropy', max_depth=3, n_jobs=-1),\n",
        "    direction='forward',\n",
        "    scoring='roc_auc',\n",
        "    tol=0.005,\n",
        "    n_jobs=-1\n",
        "    )),\n",
        "    ('autogluon', AutoGluonSklearnWrapper(label=label,\n",
        "                                    predictor_args={'problem_type': 'binary',\n",
        "                                                    'eval_metric': 'roc_auc',\n",
        "                                                    'path': wrapper_model_folder},\n",
        "                                    fit_args={'holdout_frac': 0.2,\n",
        "                                                'excluded_model_types': ['KNN', 'NN_TORCH'],\n",
        "                                                'presets': 'medium_quality',\n",
        "                                                'time_limit': 180}))\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "global_set_seed()\n",
        "\n",
        "ag_model_wrapper_method.fit(X = train_data_wide.drop(\n",
        "                    columns=[label] + ['PROSPECTID', 'campaign_id', 'direct_mail_flag']),\n",
        "                        y = train_data_wide[label])"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-fit-wrapper-method-model",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Check leaderboard using the test set."
      ],
      "id": "1fffd0b2"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: lab01-transform-wrapper-test-data\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data_wrapper = ag_model_wrapper_method[:-1].transform(test_data_wide.drop(columns=[label] + ['PROSPECTID', 'campaign_id', 'direct_mail_flag']))\n",
        "preprocessed_test_data_wrapper[label] = test_data_wide[label]\n",
        "\n",
        "df_leaders_wrapper_method = ag_model_wrapper_method.named_steps['autogluon'].predictor.leaderboard(preprocessed_test_data_wrapper)"
      ],
      "id": "lab01-transform-wrapper-test-data",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
